# Ten&See — Project Context

Student-housing platform. Express monolith serves REST API + static frontend.
MongoDB (Mongoose), Socket.io live chat with agent queue, WhatsApp Cloud API, SMTP email.

## Map (do not re-discover this)

- `backend/server.js` — entry; Socket.io handlers, chat queue init, lead-alert cron
- `backend/routes/` — 14 routers: admin (has `authMiddleware`), leads, bookings, listings,
  properties, chat, chatQueue, whatsapp, notifications, reports, analytics, audit, tasks, push
- `backend/models/` — Lead, Booking, Listing, Property, ChatMessage, ChatSession, Admin,
  Task, Notification, auditlog
- `backend/services/` — chatQueue (546 lines, SLA queue engine), chatPager, whatsapp, email
- `frontend/` — vanilla HTML/JS: index (2.6k lines), listings, listing, property,
  admin/index.html (5.9k lines, whole dashboard in one file)

## Known pitfalls

- Email module exists in 3 places; ONLY `backend/services/email.js` is canonical
- WhatsApp Cloud API base must be `https://graph.facebook.com/<version>` (NOT instagram)
- `Lead.email` is required but WhatsApp leads have no email — handle before creating leads
- Auth: import `{ authMiddleware }` from `./admin`; public routes are ONLY: GET listings/properties,
  POST leads, POST bookings, POST chat, whatsapp webhook
- JWT secret comes from `process.env.JWT_SECRET` — never add a fallback string

## Conventions

- Responses: `{ success, data | error }`
- Real-time: get `io` / `emitToAdmins` via `req.app.get(...)`
- Audit anything admin-initiated via `createAuditLog` from `routes/audit`
